FV is still great, mainly because of the community , low population, 1 chr limit, but it does seem to have gone a little down hill on the rp from when it started (not intending to be all doom and gloom there is still a lot of rp if you look for it, just when we all started in the begining it was EVERYWHERE)<br>
<br>
For me the patch removing alignments and allowing all zone shouts/auctions impaired the atmosphere as did (although they are good as well) the channels and language changes.<br>
<br>
to quote an old addage 'if it aint broke dont fix it' but thats what they did , not because it was broke but becuase it wasnt as popular as theyd liked.<br>
<br>
Now im the first to admit i dont rp much, i would like to but its rare i get the time or the feel of being immersed in it from constant ooc tells etc, not a rant either but sometimes i wish i could turn tells off (not go afk and keep playing as theyd still be there) and get the immersive experience it was to begin with with the grping/lack of channels/language restrictions and everyone rping<br>
<br>
