<br>
Even though I wasn't here long before the nerfing patch, I miss the tougher language learning, the limited shout and auction (though I have auction off anyway), and the alignment.  I don't think they needed to keep the alignment restrictions and think giving pure choice to the player and character is good, but... they didn't have to take away the alignments for the appearance sake /cry.  <br>
<br>
I have been hit by TLC and I still think it is a good thing.  I do like that there is a reason built in to associate with a younger crowd even if it is for a mercenary reason.  Give a young one a quest and offer a prize (other than money) and faction (with you and your guild) increase at it's conclusion.<br>
<br>
Lack of No Drop... I was more frustrated by No Drop on my old server than I have ever been by TLC here.  Just like chosing to join forces with whom you think is right, so too should you be able to give goods to someone as you deem appropriate.<br>
<br>
Maturity... this server does tend to have a more mature, creative set.  Whether or not it is the majority, it is the set with whom I wish to associate.  I have been impressed by the bright minds here.  This board is like a higher subset of the server, populated by the cream of the cream.<br>
<br>
The encrochment of blue.... *sigh*.  All I can do is sigh.  I have no words to describe my sadness.<br>
<br>
-Caillou's player<br>
